Legal Terms
Privacy Policy Addendum for Republic of Korea
Scope of This Addendum
The policy on this page explains additional disclosures required by the Personal Information Protection Act (“PIPA”) and contains information about Plarium’s service within the Republic of Korea. If you are based in the Republic of Korea, the terms set out below apply to you in addition to the terms set out in our Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.
Information Sharing
Delegation of Personal Information Processing
For the performance of the services detailed in our Privacy Policy, we delegate the processing of your personal information to various service providers. The details regarding the service providers and delegated services can be found below.
Here is a list of services we may delegate to other companies, along with the companies we are likely to share your information with.
Delegated Services
Delegated Service Providers (examples)
Hosting and Cloud Services
Google Cloud
Account Integrity and Security Services
Wiz, Symantech. Axonius
Social Media Login Services
Facebook
Analytic Services
Google Analytic
Customer Support and Relationship Management
Zendesk, Twilio (service communication only)
Billing and Payment Services
Adyen, Braintree, Xsolla
Attribution
AppsFlyer
Transfer of a Personal Information to a Third Party
Plarium will share personal information with third parties only as permitted under applicable law, which includes obtaining your consent or providing information in accordance with relevant laws and regulations.
Upon obtaining your consent, Plarium may provide personal information to third parties as follows:
