Data Destruction and Retention of Personal Information
Plarium promptly destroys your personal information in accordance with internal policies and applicable laws when it is no longer needed, such as after the expiration of the retention period or the achievement of the purpose for which it was collected. If Plarium is required by law or regulations to retain your personal information beyond the retention period or the original purpose, such personal information will be transferred to a separate database (DB) or stored at another secure location. When Plarium destroys personal information, electronic files will be permanently deleted so they cannot be reproduced, and paper documents will be destroyed by shredding or incineration.
